Shift management and shift handover are crucial processes of SOC team management.
This pack's purpose is Provide a single interface for all those essential elements in one place in order to prevent loss of data in the shift handover process.




## Pack Workflow

The main components of Shift management and handover pack are:


Layout
Shift hanover playbook
Dashboard

There are two ways to trigger the Shift handover playbook:manual incident and job which they results will be displayed in the layout:

Before creating a new incident make sure to provide all the playbook inputs accordingly to your purpose and your integrated apps.
After the playbook inputs are set you can create manual incident, make sure to select the “shift handover” in the incident type selection section, then the soc manager should provide his briefing for the the in the “SOC manager briefing” section, if this section will remain empty email will be send to to the SOC manager email that provided as playbook requesting to provide the briefing.
After the incident was created all the relevant components for shift handover will be displayed under the “Incident info” tab (layout).




 


## In This Pack

The Shift management and handover content pack includes several content items.



### Automations


* [AssignToNextShiftOOO](LINK): 
Randomly assigns the incidents to users on call, This is an automation for reassigning a large number of Incidents to the next shift.   
This automation works with the other Out of Office automations to ensure only available users get assigned.
Incident Ids should be passed in as a comma separated list.


*[AssignAnalystToIncidentOOO](LINK): Assign analyst to incident with consideration of PTO, OOO, or Disabled Users.
This automation will not assign users that appear in the “OOO list “ (Settings ->     advanced -> lists).
*[OutOfOffice ](LINK):

This automation is used to add/remove users to the out of office list in XSOAR.
The OOO list in XSOAR is managing all the out of the office users, users that appear in this list will not be taken in consideration with the automations AssignToNextShiftOOO or AssignAnalystToIncidentOOO.

*[OutOfOfficeListCleanup](LINK):

Cleans the out of office list (OOO list) for XSOAR users, removing any where the off until day is in the past.   
This automation is already part of the shift handover playbook, so once the playbook will be activated by job or by manual incident the list will be cleaned up.


*[AssignallanalystsOOO](LINK):

This automation is used to assign all analysts to the incident, This automation works with the other Out of Office automations to ensure only available users get assigned.

*[GetOOOusres](LINK):


This automation is used to present all the out of office users, in addition it cleans the out of office list (OOO list) for XSOAR users, removing any where the off until day is in the past. 

*[TimeToNextShift](LINK):

This automation is used to present the time until the next shift.




### Incident Fields
There is 5 incident field - 
**Out Off The Office**
**Shift Manager Briefing**
**Shift Open Incidents**
**To Join The Meeting**
**To Start The Meeting**

### Incident Types
There is 1 incident type - **Shift handover**.

### Layout
There is 1 layout - **Shift handover** 

There are 9  sections in shift handover layout wich creating the environment for the handover, the emphasis of this layout is the communication in the shift handover process, online meeting, sending notification in apps, SOC manager briefing and display of open incidents and on-call users should give a solid ground and all the essential elements for improving the communication in the handover process.       



![Layout](LINK to image)




| Layout sections | Description |
|------------------ | ------------- |
| SOC shift manager briefing | SOC manager briefing for the shift could be provided by manual input when the incident is created or by Email if this section will be left empty in the incident creation form.  |
| Open incidents  | Displays all active incidents. |
| notification message | Sending notification in the integrated app regarding the shift handover.  |
| Online meeting | Creating an online meeting in the integrated app for remote shift handover. |  
| On call team members | Displays all the team members on call. |  
| Out of the office team members | Displays the out of the office users.  |  
| Attachments | |Here the SOC manager can attach files that he wants that will be presented in the handover. |
| To do tasks | In the to do task section you can create a task and assign to them an analyst and even set a due date. |
| War room entries | | Here you will be able to see all war room entries without leaving the layout tab. | 


## Before You Start

This pack requires that you have an active instance of mail sender integration in order to send email for SOC shift manager briefing if it wasn't provided in the incident creation form, in case that that you will not activate instance of mail sender integration the SOC shift manager briefing could be provided only when creating manual incident.     
In addition it is highly recommend to use along with the following messaging and communication apps to gain all the benefits from this pack:
Zoom - for creating online meetings for remote shift handover.
Slack/Microsoft Teams - integrate your messaging apps to improve your team communication in the handover process.
